RACE.FOOTNOTES: PIRATE RADIO stalked in the three path, was driven in the four path around the far turn, ran on while tipping in to bid in the three path passing the eighth pole, dueled with an inner foe to the wire, and prevailed. STABLE STORM broke in a tangle and was out in the five path around the first turn, prompted the pace in the four path down the backside, bid in the three path around the far turn, had to steady in upper stretch, but was already beginning to fade. CRYPTONYM broke slowly, was held up off the pace in the five path down the backside, ranged up under coaxing approaching the quarter, but drifted out to the seven path while turning into the stretch, and weakened. JAKE'S AFFECTION set the pace in the two path, was roused from just off the rail into the far turn, but yielded in upper stretch.
